# Anti-slop gate (Charles · Lucy · Steven · content)

When using **charles-linkedin-strategist**, **lucy-community-marketing**, drafting LinkedIn/email/WhatsApp/marketing copy, **or** editing Steven / product AI prose in this app:

1. Before delivery, run skill **anti-linkedin-slop** (Mr. ANTI-AI-SLOP) in ANALYZE mode on the draft (or verify runtime prompts still encode the doctrine).
2. If slop is detected, HUMANIZE, then deliver only the clean copy.
3. Treat survey-hook **hard and soft** as blocking (*j’entends souvent*, *en creusant*, 3-bullet qualification triad, *moins de X plus de Y*).
4. Never name internal personas in customer-facing output.
5. Personal skill source of truth: `~/.cursor/skills/anti-linkedin-slop/PROMPT.md`.
6. In-app Steven: doctrine lives in `src/features/steven/stevenSystemPrompt.ts` + `ANTI_SLOP_PROSE_RULE` in `src/features/ai/prompts/context.ts` — keep in sync when anti-slop evolves.
